cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of differentially private gradient descent algorithms for model fitting, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the issue of privacy, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm that involves making decisions based on the accuracy of gradient measurements, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
